'''Eddy Thomas''' (c. 1932 – April 10, 2014) was a [[Jamaica]]n [[dancer]], [[choreographer]] and [[dance education|dance instructor]]. In 1962, Thomas and [[Rex Nettleford]] co-founded the [[National Dance Theatre Company of Jamaica]] (NDTC).<ref name=ckwx>{{cite news|first=Howard|last=Campbell |title=Co-founder of Jamaican dance company, Eddy Thomas, dies at 82 |url=http://www.news1130.com/2014/04/11/co-founder-of-jamaican-dance-company-eddy-thomas-dies-at-82/ |work=[[Associated Press]] |publisher=[[CKWX]] |date=2014-04-11 |accessdate=2014-05-05}}</ref><ref name=jamaicaob>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=Eddy Thomas, NDTC co-founder, dead |url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/entertainment/Eddy-Thomas--NDTC-co-founder--dead_16460872 |work=[[Jamaica Observer]] |publisher= |date=2014-04-12 |accessdate=2014-05-05}}</ref> Before establishing the NDTC, Thomas was a member of the [[Martha Graham Dance Company]] in [[New York City]].<ref name=ckwx/>
Thomas died at his home in [[Montego Bay, Jamaica]], on April 10, 2014, at the age of 82.<ref name=ckwx/><ref name=jamaicaob/>
