'''Jeff Hiller''' is an American actor and comedian.
==Life and career== Hiller started performing improv comedy [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre]] in 2001 where he was part of the improv teams "People People", "The Scam", "Creep" and "Police Chief Rumble".
Hiller has appeared in various television series, including ''[[Guiding Light]]'', ''[[Ugly Betty]]'', ''[[30 Rock]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]'', ''[[Psych]]'', and ''[[Community (TV series)|Community]]''.<ref name="usa1"/> He has also appeared in the films ''[[Morning Glory (2010 film)|Morning Glory]]'' and ''[[Ghost Town (2008 film)|Ghost Town]]''. He was well-received for his performance as [[John Quincy Adams]] in the hit [[rock musical]] ''[[Bloody Bloody Andrew Jackson]]''.
Hiller is openly gay and was founder of the all-gay improv troupe "Neely O'Hara".<ref name="ftl2"/>
