{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Julie Estelle | image = Julie Estelle (29665468002).jpg | imagesize = | caption = Estelle at the 2016 [[Toronto International Film Festival]] | birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1989|1|4}} | birth_name = Julie Estelle Gasnier | birth_place = [[Jakarta, Indonesia]] | yearsactive =2005–present | known_for = | occupation = Actress, model | spouse = | academyawards = | baftaawards = | sagawards = | awards = }}
'''Julie Estelle Gasnier''' (born January 4, 1989) is an [[Indonesians|Indonesian]] actress and model.<ref name=julie>{{cite news|url=http://en.vivanews.com/news/read/4774-julie_estelle_stop_lawan_kuntilanak|title=Julie Estelle Stop Lawan Kuntilanak|last=Maharrani|first=Anindhita|author2=Gestina Rachmawati|date=October 3, 2008|language=Indonesian|accessdate=February 27, 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130205200043/http://en.vivanews.com/news/read/4774-julie_estelle_stop_lawan_kuntilanak|archivedate=February 5, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Her first leading role in 2005 at the age of 15 was in the drama ''[[Alexandria (film)|Alexandria]]'', followed by the [[horror film]] ''[[Kuntilanak (film)|Kuntilanak]]'' in 2006 (known as ''The Chanting'' in English), and two sequels in 2007 and 2008.<ref name=making>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2008/04/12/julie-estelle-the-making-a-star.html|title=Julie Estelle: The making of a star|last=Yazid|first=Nauval|date=April 12, 2008|work=Jakarta Post|accessdate=August 19, 2009}}</ref> Although she previously said she would not make another horror film, she took a role in horror movie ''[[Rumah Dara]]'' in early 2010, and the movie was a huge hit.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2010/01/14/julie-estelle-goes-back-her-word.html|title=Julie Estelle goes back on her word|date=January 14, 2010|work=Jakarta Post|accessdate=February 27, 2010}}</ref> Internationally, she is best known for her roles as Ladya in ''[[Macabre (2009 film)|Macabre]]'' (2009) and Hammer Girl in ''[[The Raid 2]]'' (2014).
== Early life == Julie Estelle was born on January 4, 1989, in [[Jakarta]], [[Indonesia]],<ref name=julie/> the daughter of Thierry Gasnier, a [[French-American]], and Hilda Limbara, a [[Chinese people|Chinese]]-[[Indonesia|Indonesian]]. She is the second of three children. Her older sister is Cathy Sharon,<ref name=making/> a TV host and actress, and her younger sister is Charlotte Christie, a businesswoman. Estelle attended [[Lycee International Francais de Jakarta]], an International French school in Jakarta, and graduated from high school in June 2007.
== Career == Estelle began to be known since playing in the movie ''[[Alexandria]]'' (2005) which is also her first film. Through this film, Estelle was nominated as the "Most Favorite Rising Star" for [[MTV Indonesia Awards]] and won it.<ref>{{cite news|language=Indonesian|url=http://life.viva.co.id/news/read/322781-julie-estelle|title=SHOWBIZZ - Julie Estelle|work=Viva.co.id|accessdate=April 2, 2013}}</ref> She also starred in ''Dealova'', ''[[Kuntilanak]]'', and ''Selamanya''. In addition to being a model she also has appeared in several Indonesian music videos.
Estelle joined [[Gareth Evans (director)|Gareth Evan]]<nowiki/>s' ''[[Berandal (film)|Berandal]]'', the sequel of 2011 hit ''[[The Raid: Redemption]]'' as Hammer Girl,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://twitchfilm.com/2012/12/berandal-aka-the-raid-2-announces-new-cast.html|title=BERANDAL (aka THE RAID 2) Announces New Cast, More Ass Kicking|date=December 20, 2012|work=Twitchfilm|accessdate=April 2, 2013}}</ref> a female fighter proficient in [[Silat]] harimau.<ref>{{cite news|language=Indonesian|url=http://entertainment.ghiboo.com/julie-estelle-akan-perlihatkan-silat-harimau|title=Julie Estelle akan Perlihatkan Silat Harimau|date=December 27, 2012|work=Entertainment.ghiboo.com|accessdate=April 2, 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130411002900/http://entertainment.ghiboo.com/julie-estelle-akan-perlihatkan-silat-harimau|archivedate=April 11, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Evans was impressed with her acting during the casting test and decided to choose her in spite of her lack of martial arts background.<ref>{{cite news|language=Indonesian|url=http://www.antaranews.com/berita/349468/julie-estelle-jadi-hammer-girl-di-the-raid-2|title=Julie Estelle jadi "hammer girl" di "The Raid 2"|date=December 20, 2012|work=Antaranews.com|accessdate=April 2, 2013}}</ref> For the role of Hammer Girl, she trained in [[pencak silat]] under [[Yayan Ruhian]] who is also the co-choreographer of the film.<ref>{{cite news|language=Indonesian|url=http://www.joyindonesia.com/julie-estelle-ketagihan-belajar-silat/|title=JULIE ESTELLE KETAGIHAN BELAJAR SILAT!|date=February 5, 2013|work=Antaranews.com|accessdate=April 2, 2013}}</ref>
== Personal life == She had a relationship with Indonesian [[Auto race|racer]] [[Moreno Suprapto]] but broke up with him in 2008. She was featured on the cover of [[Playboy Magazine]]'s Indonesian edition in July 2006 right after she had turned 17.
